HEADWORD: Buckie
<hw>Buck"ie</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
large spiral marine shell, esp. the common whelk. See
<er>Buccinum</er>.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Deil's buckie</b></col>, <cd>a perverse, refractory
youngster.</cd> <mark>[Slang]</mark></cs> <-- sic. deil = devil. See
deil. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bucking</ent>⟦br⟧
